#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
run-cap — graphical launcher for CAP analysis jobs.

Companion to setup-cap-gui. Once you've built CAP, this is how you actually
run analyses without remembering the exact command-line incantation.

  Usage:
    ./run-cap                # open the GUI
    ./install --run          # also launches it

What it does:
  • Scans `projects/` for project directories and .ini files
  • Parses the .ini to list the top-level tasks ('RunAnalysis', 'RunDerived', ...)
  • Lets you pick output path, override event count and seed
  • Runs `bin/CAP <task> <project> <ini> <out>` as a subprocess
  • Streams stdout/stderr to a live log pane AND to logs/last-run.log
  • Stop button kills the process cleanly
  • Open-output-folder button reveals the produced ROOT files

Logs every run for later inspection.
"""
